---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Yaw Estimation";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title={`${title} | Yaw Estimation`}
  lang="en"
  prevHref={`${base}/en/control_model/`}
  prevLabel="Control Model"
  nextHref={`${base}/en/raspberry_pi`}
  nextLabel="Vision-Based Control"
>
  <article class="detail-page">
    <h1>{title}</h1>
    <p>
      A payload yaw estimation model was developed and evaluated for use in the control system, where the estimated payload yaw angle is obtained from images.
    </p>
    <nav class="page-nav">
      <div class="page-nav-row">
        <span>学習:</span>
        <a href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
        <a href="#training-data">Training Data</a>
        <a href="#targets">Detection Targets</a>        
      </div>
      <div class="page-nav-row">
        <span>Yaw Estimation:</span>
        <a href="#estimation">Yaw Estimation</a>
        <a href="#evaluation">Accuracy Evaluation</a>
        <a href="#comparison">Baseline vs Auto</a>
        <a href="#max-error">Largest Error</a>
      </div>      
    </nav>    

    <section id="workflow" class="content-section">
      <h2>Workflow</h2>
      <p>
        Training data were generated from the control evaluation results (CSV files) and used to train the payload yaw estimation model.
      </p>
      <figure class="flow-figure">
        <img
          src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/yaw_model_flow_en.png`}
          alt="Yaw 角の推定モデルの学習から推論および評価までの流れ"
        />
        <figcaption>
          Workflow of payload yaw estimation model training, estimation, and evaluation.        
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section id="training-data" class="content-section">
      <h2>Training Data</h2>
      <p>
        Training images were generated from the downward-facing camera mounted on the controller.
        Three payload types were captured under various disturbance conditions,
        and the hook positions were used as the ground truth.      
      </p>
      <div class="controller-layout">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/control.png`}
            alt="Downward-facing camera mounted on the controller"
          />
        </figure>
        <figcaption>
        </figcaption>            
      </div>
      <p>
        The training dataset was created from images captured by the downward-facing camera
        mounted on the controller.      
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/hsteel.png`}
            alt="HSteel paload"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">HSteel (2-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/plate.png`}
            alt="Plate payload"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Plate (4-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/truss.png`}
            alt="Truss payload"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Truss (4-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <p>
        <strong>
          Training was performed using two datasets, Baseline and Auto, generated under different conditions.        
        </strong>
      </p>      
    </section>

    <section id="targets" class="content-section">
      <h2>Detection Targets</h2>
      <p>
        The hooks of the HSteel, Plate, and Truss payloads are detected,
        and the payload yaw angle is calculated from the estimated hook positions.      
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/hsteel_hooks.png`}
            alt="HSteel payload with detected hooks"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">HSteel (2-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/plate_hooks.png`}
            alt="Plate payload with detected hooks"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Plate (4-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/truss_hooks.png`}
            alt="Truss payload with detected hooks"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Truss (4-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="estimation" class="content-section">
      <h2>Yaw Estimation</h2>
      <p>
        The trained model detects the hook positions,
        and the payload yaw angle is calculated from the detected hook positions.
        Even when some hooks are not detected,
        the yaw angle can still be estimated from the remaining detections.      
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/hsteel_yaw.png`}
            alt="Estimated yaw angle of the HSteel payload"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">HSteel (2-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/plate_yaw.png`}
            alt="Estimated yaw angle of the Plate payload"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Plate (4-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/truss_yaw.png`}
            alt="Estimated yaw angle of the Truss payload"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Truss (4-point suspension)</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="evaluation" class="content-section">
      <h2>Accuracy Evaluation</h2>
      <p>
        The estimated yaw angle was compared with the ground truth to evaluate estimation accuracy.
      </p>
      <div class="evaluation-layout">
        <figure class="evaluation-result">
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/yaw_eval_summary.png`}
            alt="Accuracy evaluation of payload yaw estimation"
          />
        </figure>
        <div class="evaluation-description">
          <div>
            <p>
              For the HSteel and Plate payloads, the MAE remained below approximately
              0.4° even with the Auto dataset, demonstrating high estimation accuracy.            
            </p>
            <p>
              The largest error (2.68°) was observed for the Truss payload under the
              X1Y1 disturbance condition, which was also the most challenging case in
              the control evaluation.
              See <a href="#max-error">Largest Error</a> for details.            
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="evaluation-notes">
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Data</strong>: Baseline vs. Auto</li>
              <li><strong>Object</strong>: HSteel / Plate / Truss</li>
              <li><strong>Wind</strong>: X0Y0 / X1Y0 / X1Y1</li>
              <li><strong>Images</strong>: Number of evaluation images</li>
              <li><strong>MAE</strong>: Mean Absolute Error</li>
              <li><strong>RMSE</strong>: Root Mean Square Error</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="metric-definition">
              <small>Unit: degree</small>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="comparison" class="content-section">
      <h2>Baseline vs Auto</h2>
      <p>
        The estimation accuracy was compared between the Baseline and Auto datasets.      
      </p>
      <div class="comparison-layout">

        <div class="comparison-left">
          <figure>
            <img
              src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/compare_summary.png`}
              alt="Comparison of estimation accuracy between the Baseline and Auto datasets"
            />
          </figure>
          <p>
            Most results are distributed close to the 45° line, indicating that the
            estimation accuracy is nearly identical for the Baseline and Auto datasets.
            Although the differences appear noticeable in the plot, the absolute
            errors are all below 1°, demonstrating equivalent estimation performance
            in practice.          
          </p>

          <div class="summary-box">
            The proposed image-based yaw estimation method maintained stable
            estimation accuracy even under payload oscillation and disturbance
            conditions.
          </div>
        </div>

        <figure class="comparison-right">
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/compare_chart.png`}
            alt="Scatter plot comparing estimation accuracy for the Baseline and Auto datasets"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="max-error" class="content-section">
      <h2>Largest Error</h2>
      <p>
        The causes of the largest estimation errors were investigated.
      </p>
      <p>
        The largest estimation errors occurred for the Truss payload,
        where some hooks moved outside the camera view and could not be detected.
        Even in these cases, temporal processing compensated for the missing detections,
        so the impact on the control performance was limited.
      </p>
      <p>
          A slight impact was observed only during execution on the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/raspberry_pi/#truss`}>Raspberry Pi</a>.
      </p>
      <div class="max-error-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/error_01.png`}
            alt="Missing hook detection (Frame 915)"
          />
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/yaw_estimation/error_02.png`}
            alt="Missing hook detection (Frame 920)"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .detail-page {
    padding: 32px 0 64px;
  }

  .detail-page > h1 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .detail-page > p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .page-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;

    margin: 32px 0 56px;
    padding: 16px 0;

    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .page-nav-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px 18px;
  }

  .page-nav-row span {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .content-section {
    scroll-margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 62px;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .content-section > p {
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 12px;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .figure-title {
    display: block;
    color: #222;
  }

  .controller-layout figure {
    width: 50%;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .controller-layout img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .flow-figure {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 24px auto 0;
  }

  .model-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .detail-navigation {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 24px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .detail-navigation a {
    color: inherit;
  }

  .comparison-layout {
    display: flex;
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .comparison-left {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .comparison-right {
    flex: 1;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .comparison-right img,
  .comparison-left img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .summary-box {
    margin-top: 24px;
    padding: 8px 10px;
    border: 2px solid #999;
    background: #fafafa;
  }


  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .detail-page {
      padding-top: 24px;
    }

    .page-nav {
      margin-bottom: 44px;
    }

    .content-section {
      margin-bottom: 56px;
    }

    .model-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .detail-navigation {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  .max-error-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 28px;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }

  .max-error-grid figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .max-error-grid img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .evaluation-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.2fr 0.8fr;
    gap: 36px;
    align-items: start;
    margin-top: 24px;
  }

  .evaluation-result {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .evaluation-result img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .evaluation-description {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 40px;
    min-height: 100%;
  }

  .evaluation-description p {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .evaluation-notes ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
  }

  .evaluation-notes li {
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .metric-definition {
    margin-top: 24px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .evaluation-layout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .evaluation-description {
      gap: 24px;
    }
  }  
</style>